I've just seen this happen also.

Using Eclipse 3.1 release build, CDT 3.0.0 build, a freshly ghosted Windows XP machine.

When you go to create a Managed build project, when you press Next after selecting "Managed Build Project" then nothing happens (the SWT exception is thrown at this point). Clicking Next again goes onto the next pane, but it is blank. Resizing the wizard at this point makes the widgets appear. Typing a project name and hitting Next again causes the marginTop exception to be thrown - but nothing happens. Clicking Next further has no effect.
